Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @British chicken thighs{2} in a #mixing bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cut the @broccoli{1/2%head} into florets (small trees) and add to the bowl. Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). In a #small bowl{}, mix together the garlic, @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @soy sauce{1%tbsp}. Add half of this marinade to the mixing bowl with the chicken and broccoli. Stir through to ensure an even coating.

Spread the chicken and broccoli out on a #baking tray{} along with any marinade from left in the mixing bowl. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the broccoli is tender and the chicken is cooked, giving everything a shake halfway through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, boil the @water{350%ml} in a #large saucepan{} over high heat.

> TIP: Your pan needs to be big enough to cook both the rice and the sugar snap peas!

Add the @chicken stock powder{2%tsp} and stir to dissolve. Once boiling, add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cover with a #lid{}. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

After 10 mins, remove the pan from the heat and add the @sugar snap peas{100%g}. Pop the lid back on and set aside for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice and sugar snaps will finish cooking in their own steam.

> This next bit is optional, if you don't like chilli skip straight to the final step.

Halve the @?green chilli{1}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely sliced). Get everyone around the table, dinner's 2 mins away!

Take the lid off your pan and stir the sugar snaps through the rice then share between your plates. Pour the remaining marinade over the chicken and broccoli and turn to coat. Pop the sticky chicken and broccoli on top of the rice and finish with the sliced green chilli (for the grown-ups!). Enjoy!

> TIP: Little ones may find it easier to eat if you slice the chicken thighs into strips before serving!